# IMPORTANT NOTE:
# Normally, .env files should ALWAYS be in .gitignore
# However, for this security demonstration, we ARE committing .env files
# because they contain ONLY dummy credentials for educational purposes.
# 
# In real projects: NEVER commit .env files!
# Uncomment the line below for real projects:
# .env
# .env.local
# .env.*.local